{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_47","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed with `job_failed`. Preserved work is available here:\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7017-fails-javac-compile-io.airlift-aircompressor-2.0-6c1ed703\n\nThe most likely library-specific failing stage was `compileTestJava`. The preserved Gradle logs show that the generated tests were initially written against the old `io.airlift.compress.*` API, but `aircompressor` 2.0 moved the tested classes under `io.airlift.compress.v2.*`, which caused missing-package and missing-symbol errors in `UnsafeUtilTest`, `ZstdUnsafeUtilTest`, `LzoUnsafeUtilTest`, and `SnappyUnsafeUtilTest` (`human-intervention-logs/io.airlift:aircompressor:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T21-45-56-435717Z.log`). A later attempt then failed again because it introduced `java.lang.foreign.MemorySegment`, which is still a preview API on this JDK (`human-intervention-logs/io.airlift:aircompressor:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T21-48-21-968781Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.airlift:aircompressor:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T21-52-39-588883Z.log`). After that, one runtime test still failed because `NativeLoaderTest` expected `libnative_loader_test.so`, which is not present (`human-intervention-logs/io.airlift:aircompressor:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-18T21-53-04-002863Z.log`).\n\nThe preserved metrics show the automated loop eventually converged after 5 iterations and ended at `76f3bfe3974da1fcc627931d4f05cef2522c73cc` with status `success` (`stats/io.airlift/aircompressor/2.0/execution-metrics.json`). That suggests the remaining `job_failed` was likely outside the final library fix itself. If you need to inspect the surrounding workflow failure, also check `human-intervention-logs/io.airlift:aircompressor:2.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n- Review the preserved branch diff and confirm the test updates for the `io.airlift.compress.v2` API plus the new `metadata/io.airlift/aircompressor/2.0/reachability-metadata.json`.\n- Re-run the workflow, or at minimum `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.airlift:aircompressor:2.0`, from the preserved branch to verify the fix end to end.\n- If the rerun still ends in `job_failed`, investigate the post-fix workflow path rather than the library test itself, starting with `populate_artifact_urls.log`."}}
